HEADWORD: Ladyfish
<hw>La"dy*fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A large, handsome oceanic fish (<spn>Albula
vulpes</spn>), found both in the Atlantic and Pacific oceans; -- called
also <altname>bonefish</altname>, <altname>grubber</altname>,
<altname>French mullet</altname>, and
<altname>macab⟦eacute⟧</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A labroid fish
(<spn>Harpe rufa</spn>) of Florida and the West Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ladyhood</ent>⟦br⟧
